- provide(:title, page_title(['Learning','Resources']))

%h1 Keep on learning! Here are some ways to do it.
%h2 You attended a RailsBridge workshop! That's wonderful! Wondering what to do next?
%p This is the most important thing:
%h3 Pick your next project: a tutorial, a class, or building your own app, and GET STARTED!
%p Also:
%ul
  %li Keep in touch with the people you connected with at your workshop. Coding with other people around is really motivating, plus you get to help each other solve trickier stuff.
  %li Come back to another workshop as a student, TA, or teacher. You will definitely learn more, and teaching is a really great way to learn, too. (For those who are new to this: you'll be prepared to TA sooner than you think, so don't be shy! We need you!)
%h3 Resources for you
%p There are too many wonderful resources to count, but we've gathered a few of our favorites here.
%h4 Background
%ul
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://railsapps.github.io/what-is-ruby-rails.html", :target => "_blank"} What is Ruby on Rails?
    — in-depth primer introduces basic concepts and explains why Ruby on Rails is popular
%h4 Want to learn more Ruby?
%ul
  %li
    Our
    %a{:href => "http://docs.railsbridge.org/workshop/ruby_for_beginners"} Ruby Programming for Beginners
    curriculum — includes project exercises
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://rubymonk.com/"} Ruby Monk
    — Ruby lessons & tutorials.
  %li
    Sarah Allen's & Alex Chaffee's
    %a{:href => "http://testfirst.org/"} TestFirst.org
    — learn Ruby or JavaScript the test-driven way.
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://rubykoans.com/"} Ruby Koans
    —  a lovely interactive way to test what you know about Ruby so far.
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://ruby.learncodethehardway.org/"} Learn Ruby the Hard Way
    — a Ruby port of Zed Shaw's introductory programming tutorial Learn Python the Hard Way.
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://codelikethis.com/lessons", :target => "_blank", :title => "Code Like This Lessons"} Code Like This (Ruby)
    – slides and videos teaching Ruby, linked to
    %a{:href => "http://testfirst.org/learn_ruby", :target => "_blank", :title => "Learn Ruby Test First"} TestFirst Labs
%h4 These Ruby books will knock your socks off:
%ul
  %li
    Chris Pine's
    %a{:href => "http://www.amazon.com/dp/0976694042/ref=nosim?tag=rubydocorg-20&linkCode=sb1&camp=212353&creative=380549"} Learn to Program
    — explains Ruby from the very beginning; includes great challenges & exercises.
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.amazon.com/Programming-Ruby-1-9-Pragmatic-Programmers/dp/1934356085"} Programming Ruby
    (a.k.a "The Pickaxe Book") — a comprehensive reference of the Ruby language. A good second or third book on Ruby.
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.amazon.com/Eloquent-Addison-Wesley-Professional-Series-ebook/dp/B004MMEJ36"} Eloquent Ruby
    — focuses on writing idiomatic Ruby rather than programming skills or concepts.
%h4 Want to learn more Rails?
%ul
  %li
    Our
    %a{:href => "http://docs.railsbridge.org/curriculum/"} Ruby on Rails
    curriculum
  %li
    %a{:href => "https://tutorials.railsapps.org/rails-tutorial", :target => "_blank"} Rails Tutorials
    — recommendations for a Rails tutorial to suit your skill level and learning style
  %li
    Michael Hartl's
    %a{:href => "http://ruby.railstutorial.org/ruby-on-rails-tutorial-book"} Ruby on Rails Tutorial
    — a highly recommend next step after a RailsBridge workshop to cement and further your understanding of Rails.
  %li
    Envy Labs'
    %a{:href => "http://railsforzombies.org/"} Rails for Zombies
    — good to know a little Ruby before this one.
%h4 These references & guides are indispensable:
%ul
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.ruby-doc.org/"} Ruby-doc.org
    — the Ruby documentation online
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://guides.rubyonrails.org/"} RailsGuides
    — well-written and organized guides to Rails
%h4 Other collections of resources:
%ul
  %li
    Our
    %a{:href => "http://pinterest.com/pvnrtmol/ruby-and-rails-resources/"} Ruby and Rails Resources
    Pinterest board — includes books, online tutorials, Meetup groups, and more
  %li
    Quora thread
    %a{:href => "http://www.quora.com/Ruby-programming-language/How-do-I-learn-Ruby"} "How do I learn Ruby?"
%h4 Beyond Ruby on Rails:
%ul
  %li
    Our
    %a{:href => "http://docs.railsbridge.org/frontend/"} Frontend (HTML, CSS, & JavaScript)
    curriculum
  %li
    Our
    %a{:href => "http://pinterest.com/eanakashima/learn-the-front-end/"} Frontend Resources
    Pinterest board
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.codecademy.com/learn"} Codecademy
    — Javascript, JQuery, and Python tutorials
  %li
