%h4 Where's awesome stuff that's local to me?
%h5 Around the San Francisco Bay Area:
%ul
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.sfruby.info"} SF Ruby Meetup
    — RailsBridge workshops, events specifically for alums to help you keep learning, and many more events (hack nights, talks, more) related to Rails or Ruby.
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.meetup.com/Women-Who-Code-SF/"} Women Who Code
    — language-agnostic group of woman coders, includes hack nights, weekly Rails & frontend study groups (and more!)
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://www.meetup.com/Girl-Develop-It-San-Francisco/"} Girl Develop It
    — classes for women, focusing primarily on frontend languages (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)
  %li
    %a{:href => "http://blazingcloud.eventbrite.com/"} Blazing Cloud
    — classes on many topics including Ruby, Rails, and testing. Scholarships available.
  %li
    %a{:href => "https://www.noisebridge.net/wiki/Noisebridge"} Noisebridge
    — non-profit hacker space with classes (including Ruby on Rails) and other events
%h5 Outside SF?
%p We've got you covered too! Ask your workshop's organizer about the learning opportunities in your area.
%h4 Of course, one more great way to learn:
%p Come back to another workshop as a student, TA, or teacher! You know more than you realize.